{
    "id": 22582,
    "title": "Opinion Announcement - June 19, 2008",
    "transcript": {
        "title": "Kentucky Retirement Systems, et al. v. Equal Employment Opportunity Commission",
        "duration": 262.792,
        "sections": [
            {
                "start": 0,
                "stop": 262.792,
                "byte_start": 104692,
                "byte_stop": 0,
                "turns": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "stop": 262.792,
                        "byte_start": 104692,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15139,
                            "name": "Stephen G. Breyer",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/stephen_g_breyer",
                            "last_name": "Breyer",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2785,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 775890000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2785"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32682,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49908,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/stephen_g_breyer_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 7777,
                            "identifier": "stephen_g_breyer"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 6.767,
                                "byte_start": 104692,
                                "byte_stop": 131859,
                                "text": "Well now, the second one, Kentucky Retirement Systems v. EEOC is more complicated."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 6.767,
                                "stop": 17.4,
                                "byte_start": 131859,
                                "byte_stop": 174387,
                                "text": "It involves a very complicated retirement pension system that Kentucky has so I\u0027ll simplify it for discussion and if you want the whole complication, you have to read the opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 17.4,
                                "stop": 29.242,
                                "byte_start": 174387,
                                "byte_stop": 221721,
                                "text": "The system permits, but it doesn\u0027t require, certain workers like policemen to retire at age 55 and get a pension."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.242,
                                "stop": 46.488,
                                "byte_start": 221721,
                                "byte_stop": 290684,
                                "text": "Now, for a worker who becomes seriously disabled before he be 60 \u2013 before he becomes 55, he gets a pension too because Kentucky does that by pretending that the worker had worked till the age of 55."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 46.488,
                                "stop": 54.258,
                                "byte_start": 290684,
                                "byte_stop": 321822,
                                "text": "So he gives the -- they give the worker credit for years of work that he didn\u0027t actually work and I call those phantom years."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.258,
                                "stop": 64.839,
                                "byte_start": 321822,
                                "byte_stop": 364140,
                                "text": "And if you\u0027re disabled before you\u0027re 55, you get these phantom years to bring you up to the age 55 and then they figure out what the pension would have been if he\u0027d really done it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.839,
                                "stop": 72.324,
                                "byte_start": 364140,
                                "byte_stop": 394024,
                                "text": "Well in this case, a worker became seriously disabled after he was 55 and eligible for a pension."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.324,
                                "stop": 77.228,
                                "byte_start": 394024,
                                "byte_stop": 413668,
                                "text": "And he complains that Kentucky system amounts to age discrimination."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 77.228,
                                "stop": 87.259,
                                "byte_start": 413668,
                                "byte_stop": 453792,
                                "text": "He points out that Kentucky would give 55 -- give phantom years to a worker who became disabled before he reach 55, \u0022but what about me?\u0022"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 87.259,
                                "stop": 93.386,
                                "byte_start": 453792,
                                "byte_stop": 478243,
                                "text": "He says, \u0022I \u2013 I reached 55 and then I became disabled so I don\u0027t get any phantom years."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.386,
                                "stop": 101.553,
                                "byte_start": 478243,
                                "byte_stop": 510948,
                                "text": "That\u0027s seems like age discrimination just based on the fact that whether you are older or younger than 55.\u0022"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 101.553,
                                "stop": 106.355,
                                "byte_start": 510948,
                                "byte_stop": 530174,
                                "text": "Now, the Court of Appeals agreed with that, but we don\u0027t agree with that, we reverse."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.355,
                                "stop": 114.606,
                                "byte_start": 530174,
                                "byte_stop": 563193,
                                "text": "\u201cWe agree that Kentucky treated the two workers differently, but we don\u0027t think that difference amounts to discrimination because of age.\u0022"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 114.606,
                                "stop": 120.675,
                                "byte_start": 563193,
                                "byte_stop": 587435,
                                "text": "Those are the words of the ADEA, that\u0027s what the ADEA forbids, discrimination because of age."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.675,
                                "stop": 129.892,
                                "byte_start": 587435,
                                "byte_stop": 624320,
                                "text": "\u0022Rather, we think what\u0027s going on is that Kentucky is simply trying to give a pension to workers who became disabled before they reached retirement age.\u0022"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 129.892,
                                "stop": 136.092,
                                "byte_start": 624320,
                                "byte_stop": 649084,
                                "text": "Kentucky gives the phantom years to those workers because otherwise they couldn\u0027t qualify for a pension."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 136.092,
                                "stop": 145.146,
                                "byte_start": 649084,
                                "byte_stop": 685342,
                                "text": "Kentucky doesn\u0027t give phantom years to workers who became disabled after they reach say 55 because those workers already have qualified for a pension."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 145.146,
                                "stop": 148.614,
                                "byte_start": 685342,
                                "byte_stop": 699239,
                                "text": "They don\u0027t need any phantom years to become qualified."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 148.614,
                                "stop": 163.123,
                                "byte_start": 699239,
                                "byte_stop": 757231,
                                "text": "So, age is certainly a factor that ordinarily qualifies workers for a pension, but it is pension status, \u0022Are you, Mister Disabled Worker, already qualified for a pension or not already qualified for a pension?\u0022"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.123,
                                "stop": 168.288,
                                "byte_start": 757231,
                                "byte_stop": 777920,
                                "text": "That\u0027s what matters for purposes of determining whether phantom years are added."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 168.288,
                                "stop": 171.103,
                                "byte_start": 777920,
                                "byte_stop": 789205,
                                "text": "That is what explains the difference in treatment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 171.103,
                                "stop": 176.129,
                                "byte_start": 789205,
                                "byte_stop": 809267,
                                "text": "So, age is in a sense an artifact of the pension eligibility rules."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.129,
                                "stop": 180.895,
                                "byte_start": 809267,
                                "byte_stop": 828284,
                                "text": "It is not the reason or even a reason for the discrimination."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.895,
                                "stop": 191.305,
                                "byte_start": 828284,
                                "byte_stop": 869975,
                                "text": "So, we conclude Kentucky systems does not embody the sort of discrimination that Congress sought to eliminate in the ADEA, and so it doesn\u0027t fall within the statute\u0027s prohibition."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 191.305,
                                "stop": 212.449,
                                "byte_start": 869975,
                                "byte_stop": 954508,
                                "text": "Now, we have been pretty careful to limit our holding to this quite special case of differential treatment based on pension status, and pension status is a circumstance that the ADEA and the Social Security law too both treat as special, specifically authorizing age-related rules that in other areas they might bar."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 212.449,
                                "stop": 220.17,
                                "byte_start": 954508,
                                "byte_stop": 985436,
                                "text": "Now, we also list in a number of other features, quite a few features of this case that make it special for age discrimination purposes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 220.17,
                                "stop": 246.772,
                                "byte_start": 985436,
                                "byte_stop": 1091807,
                                "text": "The upshot is that where an employer treats employees differently based on their pension status and even if the pension status does depend on age, the plaintiff still has to show that that age made a difference rather than just a pension status, that it was actually motivated this discrimination or there\u0027s a reason for it that was based upon age and not pension status."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 246.772,
                                "stop": 254.061,
                                "byte_start": 1091807,
                                "byte_stop": 1120960,
                                "text": "Now, we explain this -- it\u0027s more complex even than I\u0027ve suggested and we explained it all in our decision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 254.061,
                                "stop": 262.792,
                                "byte_start": 1120960,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Kennedy has filed a dissenting opinion with which Justices Scalia, Ginsburg, and Alito have joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
